#: src/installing.md:1
msgid "Installing Redox on a Drive"
msgstr ""

#: src/installing.md:3
msgid ""
"Once you have [downloaded](./real-hardware.md#creating-a-bootable-usb-drive) "
"or [built](./coding-and-building.md#testing-on-real-hardware) your ISO "
"image, you can install it to your internal HDD or SSD. **Please back up your "
"system** before attempting to install. Note that at this time (Release "
"0.8.0), you can't install onto a USB device, or use a USB device for your "
"Redox filesystem, but you can install from it."
msgstr ""

#: src/installing.md:5
msgid ""
"After starting your _livedisk_ system from a USB device or CD/DVD, log in as "
"the user named `user` with an empty password, click on the Redox OS icon in "
"the Orbital bottom bar to open the app menu, then open the \"System\" app "
"category and click on the \"Redox Installer\" app."
msgstr ""

#: src/installing.md:7
msgid ""
"Of if you want to launch it from the terminal run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#: src/installing.md:13
msgid ""
"If you are using the `server` variant or want to use the TUI interface open "
"a terminal window and type:"
msgstr ""

#: src/installing.md:19
msgid ""
"If Redox recognizes your device, it will prompt you to select a device to "
"install on. Choose carefully, as it will erase all the data on that device. "
"Note that if your device is not recognized, it may offer you the option to "
"install on `disk/live` (the in-memory _livedisk_). Don't do this, as it will "
"crash Redox."
msgstr ""

#: src/installing.md:21
msgid ""
"You will be prompted for a `redoxfs password`. This is for a encrypted "
"filesystem. Leave the password empty and press Enter if an encrypted "
"filesystem is not required."
msgstr ""

#: src/installing.md:23
msgid ""
"Once the installation completes, power off your computer, remove the USB "
"device, power on your computer and you are ready to start using Redox!"
msgstr ""
